  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is an open-label single-center 6-month prospective clinical trial predicting
      exacerbation of COPD with wireless telemonitoring of respiratory rate, heart rate and sleep
      in patients admitted to the pulmonary ward of the Turku University Hospital due to acute
      exacerbation of COPD.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      A bed sensor SCA11H based on ballistocardiogram (BCG) will be used to wireless telemonitoring
      of respiratory rate, heart rate and sleep for six months after an acute exacerbation of COPD.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
